results.title: 0872 Live, Laugh, Love Mini Metal Top Wind Chime with Recycled Wine Bottle Ring
results.description:
🚲This chime is perfect for wind chime lovers.  We add just one wine bottle ring and a glass center to this top. This metal top makes an adorable addition to anyone's porch, patio, garden, window, or balcony. This chime is made for indoor or outdoor use. 

🚲 Size: This fun little chime is great for people who do not have a lot of room for a larger chime.  It is about a foot from top to bottom and will make a little chime when near a fan or air vent.

🚲 Shipping and Processing Time: We try to stay ahead of orders, so many of these tops have already been made. We simply have to hang the circle and marble from the top and then it will be shipped directly to the address you give us. We usually have the chime out to you within 1-2 business days. The chime will be shipped through USPS. We carefully package each chime in the box, so it will come to you in one piece. We understand accidents happen though, and if it arrives broken we can easily replace the circle for you. 

🚲 Wind chime care: While the chimes are designed to be outdoors, some care should be taken on where they are hung. They do best in areas sheltered from the wind, and on screened in porches. They also look great indoors by a vent or in a window to show off the rich color of the glass bottle. 

🚲 How it was created: We cut out the metal top on our plasma machine with one of our original designs. The metal top is powder coated, and will last for many years. The chime is then hung with a bottle ring we have melted down in our kiln, with a marble in the center. We make everything in house, and we stand behind every chime we make. 

🚲 Customization: The top will stay the same.  You can choose from the six color options.

 🚲Who we are: Bottle Benders is a small family business located in the Northeast Georgia mountains. We love what we do, and we love our wind chimes. We have been making bottle wind chimes for 50 years. We know a thing or two about how to melt wine bottles in kilns and how to hang them so they look their best. We only use wine bottles to make our chimes. We cut them like a loaf of bread, and melt the rings in our kilns (we have over 20 kilns) to make them flat. Each ring is then hung with a marble center that we have also melted down. All our metal tops are made with our in house plasma machine, and powder coated black to help them last.  Check out our full line up on our website: www.thebottlebenders.com

We also sell bottle spoon rests and art glass wind chimes in our Etsy store. Be sure to check them out!

www.etsy.com/shop/bottlebenders
